-- Hong Kong Stocks Rise as H-Shares Halt Record 12-Day Slide
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h   a n d   A l a n   W o n g
-- 2013-06-17T01:36:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-17/hong-kong-stocks-rise-as-h-shares-halt-record-12-day-slide.html
Hong Kong  stocks  rose, with a gauge
of Chinese shares trading in the city halting a record losing
streak, after valuations slumped and Morgan Stanley advised
buying HSBC Holdings Plc shares.  The  Hang Seng Index (HSI)  gained 0.5 percent to 21,075.58 as of
9:31 a.m. in Hong Kong. About four stocks advanced for each that
fell on the 50-member gauge amid trading volume 42 percent
higher than the 30-day intraday average. The Hang Seng China
Enterprises Index of mainland companies gained 0.6 percent to
9.730.92, snapping a record 12 days of declines.  To contact the reporters on this story:
